Convicted rapist and killer, Njabulo Ndlovu, will serve life in prison for his crimes. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more. Courtesy of #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Convicted rapist and killer Njabulo Ndlovu was cruel in the manner in which he carried out his crime against three generations of women in the Ndlela family. That's according to Judge Poyo Dlwati, who handed down the sentencing in the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. WATCH: Njabulo Ndlovu murdered three members of the Ndlela family Ndlovu confessed to the brutal sexual assault and killing of 65-year-old grandmother Zanele Ndlela, her daughter Smangele and her little child Zenande at their home last month. Ndlovu has been given five life sentences for the murder and rape of the family members. In handing down the sentence, Dlwati added that she didn't agree with Ndlovu's argument for a lesser sentence, citing he showed no genuine remorse for the killings.